post_text:
Runge ISD Survey:

Dear Parents/Guardians,

As we continue to wait for further guidance from the Texas Education Agency, we do know, at this point, that students will be allowed to return to campus in August. Of course CDC guidelines will be followed as well as TEA's recommendations. The first and foremost consideration will be the safety and security of our students and staff. Please respond to the short survey that we need our parents to answer. Thank you, in advance for your participation.

Whichever method you choose, please only choose “yes” to one method. All students must follow the attendance requirements as required by law. Students will be counted present or absent when they log into the classroom and attend each class period. The Runge ISD grading policy, pre-Coronavirus, will be used for the new school year.

Please complete this survey by July 10th.

Visit our website to complete the survey.

https://www.rungeisd.org/vnews/display.v/ART/5ef3a45ca4244

post_text:
Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.

P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year.

For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

post_text:
Pre-K and Kindergarten Pre-Registration

Attention Parents:
If you have a child entering Pre-K or Kindergarten for the 2020-2021 school year, please contact Karissa Green, Runge Elementary Secretary, by Monday, June 8, 2020 to turn in pre-registration paperwork. If you have not picked up a pre-registration packet yet, please contact Mrs. Green before this date.

Pre-registration packets are only required for those entering Kindergarten if the student did not attend Pre-K at Runge Elementary during the 19-20 school year.

Per TEA guidelines, students must be "four years of age on or before September 1 of the current school year" to be eligible to qualify for Pre-K.

830-239-4315 ext. 302 (please leave a voicemail if no answer)

greenk@rungeisd.org

School Closing:

Dear Runge ISD Staff, Students, and Parents/Guardians,

As the local situation and government response to COVID-19 continues to rapidly evolve, we are monitoring all information and making adjustments to our flexible plans.

Per Policy EB (Local), I am declaring an emergency shutdown until further notice.

At this time, we will have very limited staff reporting to work. Instructional packets and lunches will still be provided to the students.

We will continually monitor this situation and will do our best to provide updates as they become available.

I know we are in uncertain times and many questions remain. In the face of that uncertainty, I am confident Runge ISD and the community it serves will work together to meet the needs of our students. I appreciate all of your support.

Respectfully,
Linda Bettin

Good evening,

I wanted all to know that we are in daily communication with TEA and its guidance about Covid 19. At this time, we will move forward as scheduled. This could change tomorrow. If a decision to close is warranted, we will communicate and post this information as soon as possible.

Regards,
Linda Bettin
Interim Superintendent

We are proud to announce that our Twirling Ensemble consisting of Rayanna Reyna, Lacey Olveda, Kailee Green, and Leilani Winpigler received a first division rating at the Regional UIL Solo and Ensemble Contest in Cuero this past Saturday. This rating has qualified the ensemble to the STATE competition which will be held at the end of May. Lacey Olveda also received a first division rating on her solo and will advance to state as well. Please congratulate these girls!

As for our musicians we had two members of the Runge Yellow Jacket band compete this past Saturday as well. Senior Silas Olveda received a 2 on his Class 1 Guitar solo and Freshman Antonio Lopez received a Superior Rating on his Class 3 Tuba solo! Please congratulate these guys!

That is not all... Our Runge Colorguard competed this Saturday as well at the Harlandale Indoor Colorguard Competition and brought home 1st place! Members of the guard are Arek Gamboa, Antonio Lopez, Xavier Rodriguez, Kailee Green, and Rayanna Reyna. Please congratulate these hard working students.

post_text:
Incident Today.

Good evening,

I want to put out an official statement about a threat made at school today. A high school student made a terroristic threat to another student. Other students heard the threat and reported it to the teacher. In turn, the teacher reported it to the office. The Sheriff’s Office was immediately contacted and they quickly responded. The high school student was cooperative and had no weapon with him. However, he did make a verbal terroristic threat. After law enforcement investigated the incident, the young man was arrested. This person was also the one that stated that he was going to shoot up the school tomorrow. He is unable to do that. He is in jail now. I want to commend the students who heard the threat for doing the right thing and reporting it immediately to an adult on campus. In this day and age, we will not take any threat lightly. The safety and security of all our students and staff is top priority.

Linda Bettin
Interim Superintendent
Runge Independent School District

Christmas Music Programs:

This year there are 2 Christmas Music Programs.

The first is for our elementary grades PreK/K through 5th Grade Music Classes. The Runge Elementary Music Concert will be on Thursday, December 6, 2018 @ 2:30 pm in the afternoon in the Runge ISD Auditorium.

The second will feature our band programs with a Christmas Concert presenting our 6th Grade Band, 7th Grade Band, and HS Band. The Band Christmas Concert is on Thursday, December 13, 2018 @ 7:00 pm in the RISD Auditorium at 7:00 pm.

We hope to see you there!

Reading Volunteer Program

We are again looking for volunteers to read with/to our elementary students.

Prospective volunteers need to be willing to invest a minimum of 30 minutes to an hour a week with our students. It is also VERY important that volunteers be able to fulfill their obligation on a regular weekly basis. Volunteers will be assigned a specific student to work with.

Prospective volunteers will have to answer a short questionnaire and agree to a criminal background check.

If you are interested, please contact:
Sally Esparza
830-239-4315 Ext:400
cesparza@rungeisd.org

Homecoming Week 2018:

Monday, September 17, 2018: MARVEL MONDAY- We’re ready to save the day! Wear your SUPERHERO gear to defeat those Lions.

Tuesday, September 18, 2018: TWIN TUESDAY- Be ready to DOUBLE DOWN on that Victory! Find your BFF and wear the same clothing.

Wednesday, September 19, 2018: Way Back Wednesday- Let’s send the Lions WAY BACK to the end of the line! Wear clothes from PAST decades.

Thursday, September 20, 2018: CLASS COLOR DAY- Show the LIONS all the Colors of Victory! Wear the picked out class COLOR.

Friday, September 21, 2018: SPIRIT DAY - JACKET PRIDE + JACKET SPIRIT = VICTORY! Wear your PURPLE and GOLD.

Homecoming Parade will be on September 20, 2018 at 7:00 p.m., followed by the Blackout Pep Rally. Homecoming Pep Rally will be September 21, 2018 at 8:00 a.m.
